sentences: Born in Winnipeg in 1960, Werner attended the St. John's-Ravenscourt School.
Werner is a founding member of Canadian country rock band Haymaker, founded in 2007.

Werner practiced Entertainment law with the firm Sanderson, Taylor (now Sanderson Entertainment Law), where his clients were The Philosopher Kings, Chris Smith Management, Sky, Ron Sexsmith and Sass Jordan.
In 1997, Werner founded Venus Corporation with Beau Randall.
From 2003-2008, Werner was one of the judges on Canadian Idol (in which capacity he appeared on a 2004 episode of Corner Gas).
From 2003-2008, Werner was one of the judges on Canadian Idol (in which capacity he appeared on a 2004 episode of Corner Gas).
He was also a judge on the 2003 one-off performance show, World Idol.
In 2011, Werner formed Zack Werner Idol School providing vocal performance training and mentoring across Greater Toronto and producing live concerts.
In 2013, he played a small role in the film Catch a Christmas Star.
In 2013, he played a small role in the film Catch a Christmas Star.
In 2016, Werner moved his Idol School to St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador.
In partnership with The Telegram and NTV (CJON-DT), he produced a province-wide singing contest for three years, Sing NL.
In 2021, Werner returned to Toronto to work in business development/affairs in the digital rights and music publishing industry.
